	* render/imagebuffer.cpp: Fix LOD in new sampling code, and
	  partially fix CSG.

2005-04-13 06:47  pgregory

	* render/: imagebuffer.cpp, kdtree.h, occlusion.h, points.h: Some
	  work on occlusion culling in the new KDTree sampling system.

2005-04-12 22:49  joron

	* render/: bucket.cpp, bucket.h, imagebuffer.cpp, imagebuffer.h,
	  imagepixel.cpp, imagepixel.h, kdtree.h, occlusion.cpp,
	  points.cpp, points.h, stats.h:

	  bucket.cpp, bucket.h CombineElement() receive pre compute
	  zthreshold,	filterdepth so imagepixel.cpp imagepixel.h will
	  remove some superficious   computation.

	  imagebuffer.cpp, imagebuffer.h keep track of the current
	  zthreshold, filterdept and the eyesplits values so the
	  RenderImage() doesn't have to compute them all the time.  stats.h
	  make sure the texturememory counter is never negative
	  occlusion.cpp, kdtree.h, points.cpp, points.h  make sure they
	  compiled on NT and MacOSX (gcc 3.3)

2005-04-11 23:57  pgregory

	* render/: kdtree.h, occlusion.cpp: Only initialise the occlusion
	  KDTree once, then for subsequent buckets, just recalculate the
	  bounds. This may result in very slightly overlapping nodes, but
	  won't affect things much, if at all.

2005-04-11 20:16  pgregory

	* render/: bound.h, imagebuffer.cpp, imagebuffer.h, imagepixel.cpp,
	  imagepixel.h, kdtree.h, occlusion.cpp, occlusion.h, points.cpp,
	  points.h: Implement alternative sampling method, using a KDTree
	  to determine which samples to test against. Experimental, enable
	  using

	      Option "Optimise" "integer Sampling" [1]

2005-04-09 03:02  joron

	* libshaderexecenv/shadeops.cpp:

	  An optimization for normalize() shadeops. I verify if the normal
	  vector would not be the same over the grid. In case of flat
	  patchs it is a big gain of performance. Idem for polygons.

2005-04-08 23:17  joron

	* libri2rib/: output.cpp, output.h:
	  Implement the new Condition RI C Binding.

	    These files needed to be modified so librib2, librib2ri,
	  libri2rib, libaqsis
	    will know about the new C Binding RIB commands. The command
	  based on the releasenote 10 of
	   Prman; are
	       RiIfBegin(string condition), RiIfEnd, RiElse,
	  RiElseIf(string condition).

	    The parser calls the right RiIfBegin()...; and each new
	  commands will call
	   TestCondition(condition) implement in the subsequant checks-in.

	    It support math and logical arithmetic for float, integer,
	  color, point, vector, normal
	  and  support direct comparaison with string.

	    see the new module condition.cpp/condition.h

2005-04-08 10:55  joron

	* render/api.xml:

	  Implement the new Condition RI C Binding.

	   These files needed to be modified so librib2, librib2ri,
	  libri2rib, libaqsis
	   will know about the new C Binding RIB commands. The command
	  based on the releasenote 10 of
	  Prman; are	 RiIfBegin(string condition), RiIfEnd, RiElse,
	  RiElseIf(string condition).

	   The parser calls the right RiIfBegin()...; and each new commands
	  will call
	  TestCondition(condition) implement in the subsequant checks-in.

	   It support math and logical arithmetic for float, integer,
	  color, point, vector, normal and
	  support direct comparaison with string.

	   see the new module condition.cpp/condition.h

2005-04-08 04:18  joron

	* render/libaqsis.dsp:

	  add condition.cpp, condition.h.

2005-04-08 04:12  joron

	* render/: condition.cpp, condition.h:

	  Implement TestCondition() calls by RiIfBegin() and RiElseIf().

2005-04-08 04:09  joron

	* libri2rib/output.h, libri2rib/ri.cpp, librib2/librib.h,
	  librib2/parser.yxx, librib2/scanner.lxx, librib2ri/librib2ri.cpp,
	  librib2ri/librib2ri.h, librib2stream/librib2stream.cpp,
	  librib2stream/librib2stream.h, render/Makefile.am, render/ri.cpp:


	  Implement the new Condition RI C Binding.

	  These files needed to be modified so librib2, librib2ri,
	  libri2rib, libaqsis will know about the new C Binding RIB
	  commands. The command based on the releasenote 10 of Prman; are
	   RiIfBegin(string condition), RiIfEnd, RiElse, RiElseIf(string
	  condition).

	  The parser calls the right RiIfBegin()...; and each new commands
	  will call TestCondition(condition) implement in the subsequant
	  checks-in.

	  It support math and logical arithmetic for float, integer, color,
	  point, vector, normal and support direct comparaison with string.

	  see the new module condition.cpp/condition.h

