2005-04-01 05:46  joron

	* libshaderexecenv/shadeops.cpp:

	  slightly faster occlusion(); it reads once the matrices, instead
	  of reading constantly the same matrix information it reads at the
	  beginning until you change the occlusion map.

	  complete match() if you have already install regular expression
	  (linux, macosx have it by default); otherwise match() stays
	  nearly the same only faster.

2005-04-01 05:37  joron

	* render/: environment.cpp, ri.cpp, texturemap.cpp, texturemap.h:

	  astyle environment.cpp texturemap.cpp texturemap.h deal with
	  cotangent information saved by ri.cpp for cube environment map
	  ri.cpp save the cotangent (as 3delight, air, ....)

	  Right now the cube texturemapping is very close to 3delight. It
	  is getting.

2005-04-01 05:29  joron

	* librib2/bdec.cpp:

	  A few months ago bdec.cpp was able to be faster but introduce
	  some bugs with gzipped and/or binary rib files. I decided to let
	  the same enhancement but it will only available if  you set
	  "IGNOREGZ" environment variable. Otherwise it remains as before.

2005-04-01 05:22  joron

	* libshadervm/shadervariable.h:

	  Varying string variables will act as uniform string variables.

2005-04-01 05:07  joron

	* plugins/tga2tif/: Makefile.am, tga2tif.c: [no log message]

2005-03-31 01:59  joron

	* aqsis/aqsis.cpp:

	  make sure it works for both posix, macosx.

2005-03-30 15:48  pgregory

	* aqsis/aqsis.cpp, render/libaqsis.def: Added a flexible catch all
	  option to the aqsis command line options.

	  --option "<any RIB request>"

	  You can specify multiple --option's on the command line, each
	  containing a string representing a RIB request. These will all be
	  parsed and executed just before the WorldBegin.

	  example:

	  aqsis --option "ShadingRate 20" --option "Format 400 400 1"
	  --option "PixelFilter \"gaussian\" 10 10" vase.rib

2005-03-30 12:10  pgregory

	* Renderer.dsw, aqsis/aqsis.cpp: Add a --res option to aqsis CL
	  renderer.

2005-03-30 11:55  joron

	* libcodegenvm/Makefile.am:

	  add a reference to ../render directory in order to find version.h

