	  of the autotools build

2005-03-24 03:52  joron

	* render/: ri.cpp, texturemap.cpp, environment.cpp, texturemap.h:

	  Make sure environment() behaved. Cube' environment GetSample()
	  was rewritten based on Pixie code, old implementation and the new
	  implemantation for MipMap GetSample().

	  In environment for cube; it will support:

	  Filter at runtime ("filter" "gaussian") PixelVariance
	  Bilinear/Trilinear sampling

	  Both latlong and cubic environment file are directly compatible
	  with others renderer's latlong/cubic tiff files.

	  You could use now teqser/aqsis to generate environment
	  latlong/cube for others renderer and aqsis could read the ones
	  generated by others.

2005-03-19 12:04  joron

	* configure.ac:

	  Until I found a way to configurate if the user has OpenEXR I
	  remove the build of d_exr, and exr2tif.

2005-03-14 05:07  joron

	* configure.ac:

	  add d_exr display support.

2005-03-14 05:04  joron

	* configure.ac:

	  add bmp2tif, exr2tif support.

2005-03-14 04:59  joron

	* plugins/Makefile.am:

	  add two new plugin bmp2tif, exr2tif.	bmp2tif is windows bitmap
	  plugin exr2tif is OpenEXR plugin for aqsis.

2005-03-14 04:57  joron

	* plugins/bmp2tif/: Makefile.am, bmp2tif.c: bmp2tif plugin

2005-03-14 04:31  joron

	* plugins/exr2tif/: Makefile.am, exr2tif.cpp:

	  First version of the importer for OpenEXR file; it convert RGBA
	  channels information (could be into Half, or Float format) and
	  create unsigned char information with gamma correction (set as
	  0.0).

	  If you have GAMMA environment variable set to any value between
	  -20 ... 20.0 it will apply that value as correction instead.

2005-03-14 04:26  joron

	* d_exr/: Makefile.am, d_exr.cpp, dspyhlpr.c, dspyhlpr.h, tst.rib:
	  OpenEXR Display

2005-03-12 20:05  joron

	* libslparse/typecheck.cpp:

	  Protect againts Null pointer.

2005-03-12 19:58  joron

	* render/texturemap.cpp:

	  I removed Trilinear filtering by default; and only let it when
	  the user sets it by "Option" "texture" "lerp" 1.

	  It solved the problem with too much blurry texturemapping...	eg.
	  the problem described by Tim (blurry.rib,sharp.rib).

	  Also I make sure BiLinear() checks if the mipmap is valid before
	  access its individual pixel...

2005-03-11 13:07  joron

	* render/stats.cpp:

	  stats.cpp : remove the division by zero into stats.cpp when you
	  don't have either primitives or curves, procedurals primtives. I
	  also from the totol timing SampleTexture which is already
	  accounted withing different shaders timers.

