2005-02-24 16:05  pgregory

	* INSTALL: Add prerequisites list.

2005-02-24 00:18  pgregory

	* Makefile.am, render/imagebuffer.cpp, render/micropolygon.cpp,
	  render/micropolygon.h, render/points.cpp, render/points.h,
	  render/quadrics.cpp, render/ri.cpp, render/shadowmap.cpp,
	  render/texturemap.cpp, render/texturemap.h: Merged fix for
	  #1144077 from the 1.0 mainenance branch.

	  Commit Michel Joron's changes to texture mapping, comment from
	  Michel...

	  ---------- Improved a lot the texturemap.cpp, texturemap.h 1)
	  GetSampleSgle() is renamed GetSampleWithoutBlur()	 within
	  this function now the sampling supports runtime filter changes
		 eg. texture(s,t,"filter","gaussian")	   the number of
	  samples is configurable	    eg.  texture(s,t,"samples", 64)
	       wih or without out trilinear() sampling		 eg.
	  texture(s,t, "lerp", 0)

	       It uses a method CalculateLevel() to figure which mipmap
	  level is
	  required; CalculateLevel() caches numerous infromation within
	  CqTextureMap, in prime it used now fastlog2().

	  2) GetSampleTri() is renamed GetSampleWithBlur()

	       within this function now the sampling supports runtime
	  filter
	  changes	    eg. texture(s,t,"filter","gaussian")      the
	  number of samples is configurable	      eg.
	  texture(s,t,"samples", 64)

	      It uses too the same method CaculateLevel().
	  --------

2005-02-22 23:43  pgregory

	* render/: imagebuffer.cpp, micropolygon.cpp, micropolygon.h,
	  points.cpp, points.h, quadrics.cpp: Fix bug #1144077. The
	  implementation of motion blurred/DoF micropolygons using the
	  CqDetachedMicropolygon class didn't allow for the special case
	  micropolygon used for Points. The use of CqDetachedMicropolygon
	  has now been removed, and an alternative solution found.

2005-02-01 23:45  jpgrad

	* render/options.cpp: Fix for Bug 1113859 (ScreenWindow doesn't
	  work properly).

	  It seems that some minus signs were missing.	This chunk of code
	  really needs to be completely reviewed at some stage though (and
	  the stages of constructing the transformations documented *much*
	  more fully!).

2005-01-26 23:21  pgregory

	* render/ri.cpp: Fix a problem with array primitive variables on
	  RiPointsGeneralPolygons.  We triangulate the general polys and
	  produce a RiPointsPolygons, during which process we need to add
	  to any uniform and facevarying arrays to account for triangles
	  added during triangulation. We weren't taking into account the
	  lenght of each element in an array variable.

2005-01-25 23:27  pgregory

	* render/micropolygon.cpp: Minor optimisation if dPdu or dPdv are
	  not needed.

2005-01-25 23:20  pgregory

	* render/micropolygon.cpp: Fix bug #1104545, Surface derivatives
	  are 0 (on quadrics)

